<doc id="180806" wikidata="Q3391235" url="?curid=180806" title="Emilia Hazelip">
<text>Emilia Hazelip (born Emilia Espinosa, Barcelona, Spain, 18 July 1937 - Carcassonne, France, 2 February 2003) was a Catalan organic gardener, former Merry Prankster, and pioneer of the concept of synergistic gardening. Her farming methods were inspired by Masanobu Fukuoka after reading his book; &quot;The One-Straw Revolution&quot; in 1978 after it was first translated into English.

